- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper discusses program synthesis, which is a subfield of programming languages. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is likely as the paper uses a machine learning approach to learn the probabilities over the space of programs. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is possible as the paper discusses a method for improving program search, which is relevant to software engineering. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is possible as the paper discusses a system for solving problems, which is relevant to systems and control.
